                            <comment id="14060844" author="aljoscha" created="Mon, 14 Jul 2014 16:55:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I will look into it ASAP.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14060904" author="rmetzger" created="Mon, 14 Jul 2014 17:34:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Do we have test coverage for the POJO support?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14061135" author="aljoscha" created="Mon, 14 Jul 2014 20:00:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, but it seems I have to extend them once I find the reason for this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14061163" author="aljoscha" created="Mon, 14 Jul 2014 20:21:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;What are &quot;Larger Inputs&quot;. Big records, or big input data and small records? Or both?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14062059" author="aljoscha" created="Tue, 15 Jul 2014 13:37:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hmm, I cannot reproduce the error. Checked it with 124mb of lipsum input data and with 500mb of lipsum input data. Both times I started the WordCountPOJO example as is from within IntelliJ.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14062113" author="stephanewen" created="Tue, 15 Jul 2014 14:23:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As the initial message said, I got the error by running it through the command line.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can you reproduce it using the packaged WordCountPOJO.jar that is in the examples directory?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14063228" author="aljoscha" created="Wed, 16 Jul 2014 07:12:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry, I didn&apos;t read that part. Now I can reproduce the error, though I still have no idea what is causing it. (Still looking)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14064781" author="aljoscha" created="Thu, 17 Jul 2014 10:21:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I found the bug. The PojoComparator is not using the user code class loader and therefore cannot duplicate the serializer it internally uses when it need to be duplicated. The fix is simple but I will also change the PackagedProgramEndToEndITCase to use a Pojo so that this will be tested.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14064968" author="aljoscha" created="Thu, 17 Jul 2014 14:37:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed together with other bugs in &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/incubator-flink/commit/152dcde0bb0d8a56bf878dde6f4aae2d2db6c8ba&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/incubator-flink/commit/152dcde0bb0d8a56bf878dde6f4aae2d2db6c8ba&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
